  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of camp management services, non-food items and shelter solutions to displaced populations in north-east Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM aims to reach a total of 437,646 IDPs in camps and camp-like settings through a multi-sector approach, including camp coordination and camp management (CCCM), shelter, and non-food items (NFIs). The project is in line with the NHF Allocation Strategy, both in terms of activities, target locations and beneficiary types. Under the CCCM component of the project, IOM will focus on enhancing site facilitation capacity and site improvements. The shelter response will include  the construction of 1,350 emergency shelters, and the reinforcement of 1,000 shelters. Under the NFI component of the project, IOM will preposition 550 NFI kits and distribute 500 NFI kits to ensure that the immediate needs are met while enhancing preparedness for needs as they arise. The activities will be implemented in camps and camp-like settings in Ngala, Gwoza (including Pulka), Bama (including Banki), Dikwa, Monguno, Mafa, Jere, Maiduguri Metropolitan Centre (MMC), Kala Balge (Rann), and Damboa in Borno State, and Yola North, Yola South, Girie and Song in Adamawa state.</narrative>
  </description>
